Blue Bell Ice Cream has suspended operations at an Oklahoma production facility that officials had previously linked to a foodborne illness linked to the deaths of three people .
Ten products recalled earlier in March were from a production line at a plant in Brenham, Texas, the company's headquarters in Texas .
The company and health officials said a 3-ounce cup of ice cream contaminated with listeriosis was traced to a plant plant in Broken Arrow, Oklahoma .
Listeriosis is a life-threatening infection caused by eating food contaminated with bacteria called Listeria monocytogenes .